1.  About this Document

	The purpose of this document is to outline the basic rules governing group meetings, group roles, and contact information for Team VHIA.   The document elaborates on several of these topics by listing a set of agreements that all members agree to abide by, as well as penalties for missed meetings or late attendance to pre-arranged meetings.  The document has been updated to reflect the recent changes in member roles due to the start of the second quarter of this project.

2.  Member Roles and Descriptions
	
	At this point, we feel we have established the main member roles over the course of the first quarter.  At this point we are shifting our roles to reflect our contribution to the actual development of the product.  We expect group members to feel free to contribute to software development in the most effective way they can so as to produce an acceptable final product.
